1xx — Informational Responses
    These indicate that the request was received and the process is continuing.
Common 1xx Codes
==>100 Continue
The server received the request headers and the client can proceed with the body.
==>101 Switching Protocols
Server is switching to another protocol (e.g., WebSocket).
==>102 Processing
Server has received the request but is still processing it.

-->2xx — Success Responses
   These mean that the request was successfully received, understood, and accepted.
Common 2xx Codes
==>200 OK
Request succeeded; response body contains the result.
==>201 Created
A new resource was created (often after a POST).
==>202 Accepted
Request accepted for processing but not completed yet.
==>204 No Content
Request succeeded but no content returned (common after DELETE).

 3xx — Redirection Responses
  These indicate that the client must take additional action (usually a redirect).
Common 3xx Codes
==>301 Moved Permanently
Resource has a permanent new URL; search engines update links.
==>302 Found
Temporary redirect; original URL may still work later.
==>304 Not Modified
Resource not changed; client should use cached version.
==>307 Temporary Redirect
Same as 302 but does not allow method change.

-->4xx — Client Error Responses
   These indicate problems with the request from the client side.
Common 4xx Codes
==>400 Bad Request
Malformed request syntax or invalid data.
==>401 Unauthorized
Authentication required or incorrect credentials.
==>403 Forbidden
Client authenticated but not allowed to access resource.
==>404 Not Found
Resource does not exist on the server.
==>409 Conflict
Request conflicts with the current state of the resource.
==>429 Too Many Requests
Client has sent too many requests (rate limiting).

--> 5xx — Server Error Responses
    These indicate that the server encountered an error while processing the request.
Common 5xx Codes
500 Internal Server Error
==>Generic server failure.
501 Not Implemented
==>Server doesn't support the requested method.
502 Bad Gateway
==>Upstream server returned an invalid response.
503 Service Unavailable
==>Server is down or overloaded; try again later.
504 Gateway Timeout
==>Upstream server did not respond in time.
